      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "EDIT allows you to create new files and modify existing files.  You may"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "overtype any data being displayed on the screen.  When the data does not"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "fit within one screen, EDIT permits you to scroll up, down, left, and right"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "as required."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "EDIT commands fall are described as:"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "PRIMARY COMMANDS+- are entered in the COMMAND area of line 2."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "LINE COMMANDS+   - are entered by overtyping the line numbers which"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "appear at the left-hand side of the screen."
      },
